cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.AR 

This paper is primarily focused on machine learning workloads and the use of Google's Cloud TPUs for accelerating these workloads. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Julia programming language and compiler-based automatic differentiation techniques, which could also place it in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses the use of cloud computing and offloading workloads to TPUs, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
